## Formula

$SE = \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{n}}$

Alternative formulation, used in [null hypothesis significance testing]():

$SE = \sqrt{\frac{\sum e^2}{n-2}}$

Where $e$ are the residuals (differences between predicted and actual values).

